Introduction

Client side:
  1. Ubuntu 17.04  download Shadowsocks-Qt5-3.0.0-x86_64.appimage
  2. sudo chmod a+x  Shadowsocks-Qt5-3.0.0-x86_64.appimage
  3. sudo ./Shadowsocks-Qt5-3.0.0-x86_64.appimage
    
  4. Configuration
    then add connection with serverIP, serverPort, Password, keep local settings given by default and make sure SOCKS5 as local server type,
    and also make sure the correct Encryption Method correspond to the server's configuration is choosen. once click 'start', this will connect
    to the server
  
    then we need to configure the proxy in the browser
    Chrome: install SwitchyOmega, in PROXY section, choose SOCKS5 as Protocol, fill the local IP and port then apply changes. In up right side 
    of Chrome, click the switch button and choose PROXY,
  
